[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

257
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:07,267
Mm-hmm.

258
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:08,933
I have to go.

259
00:13:08,933 --> 00:13:10,933
I'm gonna be late
for my chemical peel.

260
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:12,067
Mom! Wait!

261
00:13:13,367 --> 00:13:15,233
Aren't we even
gonna do anything?

262
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:18,000
What? You're suspended, right?

263
00:13:18,533 --> 00:13:20,800
But aren't we filing a case?

264
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:23,067
[SIGHS]

265
00:13:24,067 --> 00:13:25,900
We don't have any evidence yet.

266
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:28,067
Besides, McKenna's right.

267
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,967
Even if she looks
like Goldilocks.

268
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,400
The photos will
just spread more.

269
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:36,767
Filing a case is a long process.

270
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,467
Even my annulment case
with your dad

271
00:13:39,467 --> 00:13:41,333
still hasn't gone anywhere.

272
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:43,067
You are responsible...

273
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:45,133
...for whatever you send
out there.

274
00:13:45,133 --> 00:13:47,000
I really thought
you knew better.

275
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,933
All your hard work, poof!

276
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:51,900
Gone! Down the drain!

277
00:13:53,167 --> 00:13:56,000
Just because you played dumb.

278
00:13:56,033 --> 00:13:58,433
If there's anything
that I wanted you to learn

279
00:13:58,433 --> 00:14:00,167
from when your father left us,

280
00:14:00,167 --> 00:14:03,500
it's not to be as stupid
as I was.

281
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:06,067
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

282
00:14:07,533 --> 00:14:09,967
Like mother, like daughter.

283
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:10,933
[MARLA SNIFFLES]

284
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:11,900
Mom...

285
00:14:12,933 --> 00:14:15,233
- Hm! Oh!
- I'm sorry.

286
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:18,067
Don't...

287
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:20,267
Don't drop that tear.

288
00:14:21,167 --> 00:14:23,133
Don't show that you're affected.

289
00:14:24,967 --> 00:14:26,800
The least you can do is...

290
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:28,233
Be proud of it.

291
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:30,500
- Be proud of your nude photos!
- Mom!

292
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:33,400
How can I be proud
of my nude photos?

293
00:14:34,167 --> 00:14:36,000
My life is ruined!

294
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,333
[MARLA SNIFFLING]

295
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:38,867
This is so embarrassing.

296
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:41,500
It's really embarrassing,
but don't show it.

297
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:46,167
Don't give them the luxury
of showing your tears.

298
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:48,267
Hm.

299
00:14:49,133 --> 00:14:50,567
Hold your head up.

300
00:14:50,567 --> 00:14:52,233
Hm. Show your chin.

301
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:56,300
Don't drop that tear,
don't drop that.

302
00:14:57,267 --> 00:14:58,967
And then smile.

303
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:01,567
Smile some more.

304
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:03,367
- Smile.
- Mom?

305
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:06,567
People are already staring
at us. Do it!

306
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:08,067
[BELL RINGING]

307
00:15:08,067 --> 00:15:10,033
Smile. There you go.

308
00:15:10,033 --> 00:15:11,300
Now, laugh.

309
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:15,467
[LAUGHING FORCEFULLY]

310
00:15:15,467 --> 00:15:16,567
Scandal?

311
00:15:16,567 --> 00:15:20,600
[LAUGHING FORCEFULLY]

312
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,633
Are you bothered?

313
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:24,200
Me? Bothered? No.

314
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:27,233
[LAUGHING FORCEFULLY]

315
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:28,333
Louder!

316
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:34,000
[LAUGHING FORCEFULLY]

317
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,500
I'll just move on.

318
00:15:35,533 --> 00:15:36,967
[LAUGHING FORCEFULLY]

319
00:15:36,967 --> 00:15:38,967
Thank you! Thank God!

320
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:41,200
[LAUGHING FORCEFULLY]

321
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:43,600
- You, young lady!
- Mom! That hurts!

322
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,167
- You're becoming too much.
- [PHONE RINGING]

323
00:15:47,167 --> 00:15:48,233
[PHONE RINGING]

324
00:15:49,133 --> 00:15:50,333
Hey, hey.

325
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,700
Who was that? Was it Lester?
Why didn't you answer him?

326
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:55,033
I don't want to talk to him!

327
00:15:55,033 --> 00:15:56,033
- Dear...
- Oh?

328
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:58,100
Tsk! Was that you?

329
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:00,300
It smells bad.

330
00:16:01,167 --> 00:16:02,533
Ah! No!

331
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,567
Why didn't you answer him?!

332
00:16:04,567 --> 00:16:07,367
Where else will you find
a good guy?

333
00:16:07,367 --> 00:16:11,933
He's smart, kind,
and, most importantly, rich!

334
00:16:11,967 --> 00:16:14,567
He's our ticket
out of poverty, right?

335
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:17,667
Mom, I can do that myself!
I'll do even better in school!

336
00:16:19,167 --> 00:16:21,200
I'll be able to study abroad!

337
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:25,567
I'll find a good job
that pays well!

338
00:16:25,567 --> 00:16:27,667
- We don't need Lester!
- Grace...

339
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,067
Did I say you could talk?

340
00:16:32,167 --> 00:16:33,600
Dessalyn, first of all,

341
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:36,467
being smart won't get you
ahead in life.

342
00:16:36,467 --> 00:16:40,500
Okay? What, you're going abroad?
You'll work?

343
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,100
But in the end,

344
00:16:42,133 --> 00:16:44,467
it's still a man
who'll carry you through life!

345
00:16:44,467 --> 00:16:48,033
When you fall in love,
you get married.

346
00:16:48,033 --> 00:16:50,500
When you get married,
you'll have kids,

347
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:52,400
and then you'll have a family.

348
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:54,267
So where will you use
your diploma by then?

349
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:57,200
Nowhere, right?
Use your brain, not just books!

350
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:59,300
- Mom. Mom! Mom!
- Shhh!

351
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:01,733
Don't you trust me?
I can do it!

352
00:17:01,733 --> 00:17:04,100
Look at your father.

353
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:06,633
He finished law school, right?

354
00:17:06,633 --> 00:17:08,300
But he still can't pass
the bar exam.

355
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:10,167
We didn't get anything
out of it.

356
00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:12,533
And now,
he's addicted to gambling,

357
00:17:12,533 --> 00:17:14,733
and we're buried in debt.

358
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:17,633
See?! Your father is no use
to us!

359
00:17:17,633 --> 00:17:18,767
[SNEEZES]

360
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:22,633
- It's like--
- Excuse me, excuse me.

361
00:17:22,633 --> 00:17:24,033
You got something to say?

362
00:17:25,167 --> 00:17:28,367
Dessa, I don't earn enough
for all of us.

363
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:31,700
We're already using your stipend
to pay the electricity bill.

364
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:33,767
And now,
you're getting suspenders?

365
00:17:33,767 --> 00:17:36,500
"Suspenders"? It's "suspended"!

366
00:17:37,267 --> 00:17:38,500
It's the same thing!

367
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:42,467
Well, you're suspended,
so what do we do now?

368
00:17:42,467 --> 00:17:44,767
I'll handle it. I'll find a way!

369
00:17:44,767 --> 00:17:49,500
You should! So call Lester now.
Talk to each other!

370
00:17:49,533 --> 00:17:53,200
I don't care about
those nude photos anymore!

371
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,500
First of all,
people will forget about that,

372
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,767
and something new will come up.

373
00:17:56,767 --> 00:17:58,667
The new thing will get
all the attention.

374
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:01,233
Besides, you're not
a celebrity or famous person,

375
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:03,067
so stop overreacting!

376
00:18:03,067 --> 00:18:05,233
Tsk. Mm...

377
00:18:05,233 --> 00:18:07,067
What-- What's your name again?

378
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:10,300
Daisy?

379
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:13,433
Daphne! Daphne!

380
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:15,800
Daphne?

381
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:20,167
Make sure you use Daphne
to the best of your ability.

382
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,467
I'm taking back
what I said earlier.

383
00:18:23,467 --> 00:18:24,400
Let's go.

384
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:26,533
Coming.

385
00:18:27,133 --> 00:18:29,400
Dear, I'm sorry
I couldn't defend you

386
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:30,567
against your mom.

387
00:18:33,367 --> 00:18:34,767
I understand, Dad.

388
00:18:34,767 --> 00:18:37,400
I'm sorry you got dragged
into this mess.

389
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:39,300
It's okay.

390
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:42,700
The important thing is,
follow what your heart wants--

391
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:44,100
Sounds like
you're saying something.

392
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:45,367
Are you talking about me?

393
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:47,133
- Nothing...
- No, we're not.

394
00:18:47,133 --> 00:18:49,100
Yes! No! Yes!

395
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:50,533
Why are your eyes so big?
Are you mad at me?

396
00:18:50,533 --> 00:18:52,867
- Are you angry?
- No. Yes.

397
00:18:52,867 --> 00:18:54,367
What were you saying about me?

398
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,733
- You've got some nerve!
- I said nothing!

399
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:58,167
See! This is what
I was telling you.

400
00:18:58,167 --> 00:18:59,867
- I'm not-- I'm not mad.
- Yes, you are.

401
00:18:59,867 --> 00:19:01,633
That's enough.
Settle that at home.

402
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,467
What do you mean I'm raising
my voice? It's my norm--

403
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:04,633
That's not true!

404
00:19:04,633 --> 00:19:06,633
This is just who I am!

405
00:19:06,633 --> 00:19:11,767
Dad, I'm sorry, Dad.
I'm sorry, Dad.

406
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:14,133
[NYX CRYING]

407
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,833
Stop saying sorry.

408
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,500
[NYX CRYING]

409
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:18,800
It's not your fault.

410
00:19:21,667 --> 00:19:22,800
I'm not angry.

411
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,733
I'm so ashamed
to face you and Dada.

412
00:19:26,733 --> 00:19:28,400
[NYX CRYING]

413
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:31,100
I'm so ashamed.

414
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:34,367
I know the sacrifices...

415
00:19:35,433 --> 00:19:41,200
...you made just to get me
into SOSH.

416
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:45,167
You might think I'm taking
your hard work for granted,

417
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:46,367
but that's not it.

418
00:19:46,367 --> 00:19:48,367
This is annoying
and embarrassing.

419
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:51,933
I'm just adopted,
and yet I act like this.

420
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:53,133
Adopted?

421
00:19:53,933 --> 00:19:55,267
Who told you that?

422
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:57,667
Did you read my diary?!

423
00:19:57,667 --> 00:19:59,167
[NYX] Dad, that's too loud.

424
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:02,200
Dad, I already know.

425
00:20:02,233 --> 00:20:03,833
You're not adopted.

426
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,267
You're my daughter.

427
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:07,433
[SIGHS]

428
00:20:07,433 --> 00:20:08,900
My baby.

429
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:10,967
You're our baby, mine and Dad's.

430
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:12,767
I don't want to hear
that again, okay?

431
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:19,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

432
00:20:19,267 --> 00:20:20,600
I don't know how...

433
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:23,533
I don't even know how
to face you anymore

434
00:20:23,533 --> 00:20:24,667
because...

435
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:26,667
I know...

436
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,567
you think differently of me now.

437
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:32,633
I'm really sorry, Dad.

438
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:36,667
I promise, I'll really do
my best no matter what.

439
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:39,767
I'll make you proud
of me again, I promise.

440
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:43,233
- Promise.
- My daughter, listen to me.

441
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:46,900
This doesn't change
how I see you.

442
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:50,733
Your Dad and I...

443
00:20:52,467 --> 00:20:54,333
we are so proud of you.

444
00:20:55,667 --> 00:20:58,600
We even brag about you
at the salon.

445
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:01,400
To our gay and middle-aged
women customers.

446
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:04,700
Future Bill Gates
and Steve Jobs, right?

447
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:06,800
[CHUCKLES]

448
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:10,000
[CRYING]

449
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,533
But, Nyx...

450
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:16,333
I hope you're careful about
who you choose to love.

451
00:21:16,833 --> 00:21:18,867
Don't confuse attention...

452
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:22,600
with connection.

453
00:21:24,367 --> 00:21:25,633
Or worse...

454
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:29,800
love.

455
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:36,600
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

456
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,800
[CRYING] Dad...

457
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:46,900
You're pretty good at these
words of wisdom, Dad.

458
00:21:54,367 --> 00:21:55,500
Stop crying.

459
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,267
Stop crying.

460
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:03,633
[VICTOR] Want me
to shave their heads?

461
00:22:05,767 --> 00:22:07,267
No, Dad.

462
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:12,500
No, Dad.

463
00:22:13,633 --> 00:22:14,933
Dad, hey!

464
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:16,933
What are you doing, Dad? Hey!

465
00:22:16,967 --> 00:22:18,500
Dad, what are you doing?!

466
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:22,100
Dad! What are you doi--
Dad!

467
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:23,733
Dad, for the love of Beyonce,

468
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:25,400
what are you doing, Dad?!

469
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,633
I'm standing by you.

470
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:29,300
If you feel like they're
stripping you bare

471
00:22:29,900 --> 00:22:31,867
then I want you to know
I'm right here with you.

472
00:22:32,933 --> 00:22:34,433
Naked?

473
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:37,100
[VICTOR] That I'm with you
and I'm protecting you.

474
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:39,400
They can look at your body
but not your soul.

475
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:41,567
So they can feast at my body.

476
00:22:42,833 --> 00:22:44,033
Dad...

477
00:22:48,667 --> 00:22:51,033
I appreciate
the statement effect.

478
00:22:51,033 --> 00:22:53,333
I loved your campy performance.

479
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:56,567
Thank you, but...

480
00:22:57,500 --> 00:23:00,000
that'll only make things
harder for me at school.

481
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,833
Let's keep you dressed up.

482
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:05,633
Fine. It's embarrassing.

483
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:07,967
[NYX] Right, a little bit...

484
00:23:07,967 --> 00:23:09,700
Put your belt back on,
that's expensive.

485
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:11,733
Close that.
Dad, please don't.

486
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:15,633
Dad, they will see
your wild side.

487
00:23:18,733 --> 00:23:25,567
[WIND CHIMES CLINKING]

488
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:26,933
[BAG THUDS]

489
00:23:32,767 --> 00:23:34,433
[LINE BEEPS]

490
00:23:34,433 --> 00:23:36,867
[ISOBEL'S DAD]<i> What am I hearing
</i> about a scandal?

491
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:39,033
<i>You know what, I don't
even want to know.</i>

492
00:23:39,033 --> 00:23:41,400
<i>I don't have time for this.
You're grown now.</i>

493
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:43,033
<i> You can take care of yourself.</i>

494
00:23:43,733 --> 00:23:46,633
<i>I won't be able to go home
to visit Mom.</i>

495
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:48,533
<i>Take care of your grandma, okay?</i>

496
00:23:48,533 --> 00:23:49,933
<i> I'll just send money.</i>

497
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:54,567
<i>Remember, Isobel, you're
responsible for your Grandma.</i>

498
00:23:54,567 --> 00:23:56,567
<i> Her life is in your hands.</i>

499
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:59,400
<i> So, please, behave yourself.</i>

500
00:23:59,933 --> 00:24:02,067
<i>Don't get involved
in any scandals.</i>

501
00:24:02,067 --> 00:24:03,300
[LINE BEEPS]

502
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:05,633
[ISOBEL'S MOM]<i> Isobel,
</i> I'm sorry if I can't be there.

503
00:24:05,633 --> 00:24:07,067
<i> I can't come home.</i>

504
00:24:07,067 --> 00:24:09,000
<i>You know how it is,
Gavin's starting school,</i>

505
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,367
<i> and your Stepdad Fred...</i>

506
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:13,867
<i>he won't let me because no one
will be left to handle things.</i>

507
00:24:13,867 --> 00:24:16,533
<i>I'm the only one managing
the business here in Canada.</i>

508
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:20,500
<i>Honey, why did you send
nude photos?</i>

509
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:22,633
<i>You should've thought about
Grandma Helen.</i>

510
00:24:22,633 --> 00:24:24,567
<i> You're all she has now.</i>

511
00:24:24,967 --> 00:24:31,967
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

512
00:24:46,667 --> 00:24:53,633
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

513
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:15,067
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

514
00:25:15,067 --> 00:25:20,133
[GLASS SHATTERING]

515
00:25:20,133 --> 00:25:24,567
[METAL THUDS]

